parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pistons can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, misfires, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle experiences misfires
the engine shakes or knocks
and the vehicle may stall or hesitate to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a loss of power, hesitation to accelerate, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts hard
the transmission hesitates to shift
the transmission slips or jerks
and the vehicle experiences a loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine piston can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The misfire can also cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk, making it difficult to control.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates
the vehicle stalls
the engine misfires
the vehicle hesitates or jerks while accelerating
the Service Stabilitrak light illuminates
and the vehicle may experience rough idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the turbocharger fails to provide boost pressure
the vehicle stalls
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto-stop feature can cause the vehicle to roll back or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls back or stalls when the auto-stop feature is engaged
the vehicle fails to restart
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injector can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the check engine light illuminates
and the vehicle experiences poor engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of critical vehicle functions, including the instrument cluster, air conditioning, and radio, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument cluster goes dark
the air conditioning and radio stop working
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
and warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto stop feature can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while in motion
the auto stop feature fails to restart the engine
and the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the remote key fob can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "no remote detected" message is displayed
the remote key fob does not work
and the vehicle does not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery dies suddenly
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction
and the vehicle does not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light can cause water to leak into the trunk and affect the vehicle's electrical systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake light cracks
water leaks into the trunk
and the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.
